The paper deals with machine learning methods for automatic measurement of pre-aspiration duration in speech signals. This involves analyzing sequences of vocalic/consonantal sonorants and phonetically voiceless obstruents. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound). The paper also involves natural language processing and speech recognition, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing). The use of machine learning algorithms also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with linguistic analysis, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Language and Vision).
